Just like the uncertainty surrounding their trip and subsequent appearance for the first leg match in north Africa the fate of the reverse fixture  is surrounded in confusionA section of the club players told Nation Sport that they will not attend any training session ahead of the match as they continue to demand for their unpaid duesOmollo said that under the current circumstances the club should forget about  overturning the 6-0 deficit A Gor Mahia players strike has persisted into the New Year as the second leg of the first round of their Caf Champions League fixture against CR Belouizdad of Algeria looms large. 

Gor host the Algerian outfit on Wednesday at Nyayo Stadium trailing 6-0 from their demolition in Algiers on Boxing Day. 

Just like the uncertainty surrounding their trip and subsequent appearance for the first leg match in north Africa the fate of the reverse fixture  is surrounded in confusion. 



